Death of Drusus. Dedication of the Precinct of Livia, the Campus Agrippae, the Diribitorium, the Temple of Mars. Tiberius retires to Rhodes. Lucius and Gaius Caesar, the natural heirs of Augustus, both die young. Influence of Augustus's wife Livia. Institution of the corps of watchmen (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">vigiles</SPAN>).
		</DIV></TD>
	</TR>

